{
  "doc_id": "41125",
  "text": "The development of efficient computing infrastructures to store and retrieve genomic information is thus an essential part of the discovery pipeline in genomic research. The UCSC genome browser [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and the Ensembl genome browser [CITATION_3] 6) were among the first systems specifically developed to address this issue and opened the access of sequencing data to the whole scientific community.",
